ed purpose is to enable the Tab Notes feature in Nightly for users who ever created a tab note. This will let those users continue to use Tab Notes without having to manually flip the tab notes pref or manually enroll in the Firefox Labs experiment for the tab notes feature.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282718\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285091\n", "files": ["browser/components/asrouter/docs/targeting-attributes.md", "browser/components/asrouter/modules/ASRouterTargeting.sys.mjs", "browser/components/asrouter/tests/browser/browser_asrouter_targeting.js", "browser/components/tabnotes/TabNotes.sys.mjs", "browser/components/tabnotes/TabNotesController.sys.mjs", "browser/components/tabnotes/test/unit/test_tab_notes.js"], "git_node": "eb8d4feddb387ff03145930dd878e86b99258639", "git_parents": ["a7ec29f07432ebf9de710c6e874fd1894ba30d69"], "node": "8d04df467917390f392b49af58493d984823f976", "parents": ["1d95df131fd072f4ebe735baea0b0fd5bbf6c800"], "tags": []}], "date": 1772184501, "git_changesets": ["eb8d4feddb387ff03145930dd878e86b99258639"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "24806": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2017482 - Make `nsHTMLCopyEncoder::GetParentPoint()` return error if shadow host is not a part of the flattened tree  a=pascalc\n\nPreviously, it (renamed from `GetNodeLocation) returned error in this\ncase [1]. Then, the callers aborted. However, now, this returns unset\npoint instead and then, the loops in `GetPromotedStartPoint` and\n`GetPromotedEndPoint` will treat as in a generated content.\n\nThe generated content handler in `GetPromotedEndPoint` is ported as-is,\nbut the now, `GetParentPoint()` cannot return only the container because\n`RawRangeBoundary` needs to be a valid point for selection. Therefore,\nthe ported code won't work.\n\nThis patch restores the behavior of `GetParentPoint` in the case.\nHowever, then, there is a discrepancy. If the loops stop due to the\npoint is not start/end of the container, it returns the promoted point\nin the shadow. However, if it reaches the host which is not part of the\nflattened tree, it returns an error so that failing to copy the\nselection. Therefore, this fixes the case in `IsRoot()`.\n\nFinally, in these days, selections shouldn't be start/end in generated\ncontent. Therefore, this patch makes them return error in the case with\nasserting in the debug builds.\n\n1. https://searchfox.org/firefox-main/rev/a1c0acfae3e40def5d80b3dc9916b07e18a85c63/dom/serializers/nsDocumentEncoder.cpp#2275-2276,2278-2279\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D284051\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285156\n", "files": ["dom/serializers/nsDocumentEncoder.cpp", "editor/libeditor/tests/test_bug1306532.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/editing/crashtests/selectall-in-contenteditable-replaced-by-shadowroot.html"], "git_node": "8919bf2b9701859790c5feaa9df548c827d01e50", "git_parents": ["eb8d4feddb387ff03145930dd878e86b99258639"], "node": "0bcf4ee228dee46daed427b2a9e23f69d79f608a", "parents": ["8d04df467917390f392b49af58493d984823f976"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_149_0b2_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_149_0b2_RELEASE", "FIREFOX-ANDROID_149_0b2_BUILD1", "FIREFOX-ANDROID_149_0b2_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_149_0b2_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_149_0b2_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1772184542, "git_changesets": ["8919bf2b9701859790c5feaa9df548c827d01e50"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "24807": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@lando.moz.tools\u003e", "branch": "tags-unified", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 0bcf4ee228dee46daed427b2a9e23f69d79f608a with FIREFOX-ANDROID_149_0b2_BUILD1 a=tagging CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": "54af7e3a4202ceaa4c972a21767a6ad060e461e9", "git_parents": ["3463e4f761d3e1ba01f8ed4f3b2798b0c3b0bbfc"], "node": "45a2eca3f556d0e95f3b4e8852cf2fc62fcd3d12", "parents": ["b