7856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nru -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nsk -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nsl -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nson -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nsq -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nsr -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nsv-SE -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nta -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nte -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nth -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\ntl -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\ntr -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\ntrs -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nuk -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nur -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nuz -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nvi -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nwo -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nxh -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nzam -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nzh-CN -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\nzh-TW -\u003e 583d612467856da5f7f555c3b967adaa420944d8\n", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": "d2c26aadb825fa2b60bbdf1501109d058decca73", "git_parents": ["4275679816f3b1bcea2eef273fd0738847d88140"], "node": "2cd5ed9817479f1b0eb35797d4d3c0274f68e6f7", "parents": ["dd44fd5a83af9d74d54044f96b71ab27dc3d70cb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773306247, "git_changesets": ["4275679816f3b1bcea2eef273fd0738847d88140", "d2c26aadb825fa2b60bbdf1501109d058decca73"], "user": "ffxbld@lando.moz.tools"}, "25037": {"changesets": [{"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2016373: Ensure the correct doc and id when setting the embedder.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D283639\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287275\n", "files": ["accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": "bf36ec337ff6fd84f86ad164f2ab44c972f01020", "git_parents": ["d2c26aadb825fa2b60bbdf1501109d058decca73"], "node": "f89353f2250a2bbef61321bcb7695dfdc67c8cc0", "parents": ["2cd5ed9817479f1b0eb35797d4d3c0274f68e6f7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2019759: Don't always treat embedding a DocAccessibleParent which already has a parent as an error.  a=pascalc\n\nThere is one case where this is actually valid: when the embedder OuterDocAccessible gets re-created, whether due to layout or some other reason.\nIn this case, PBrowserBridge::SetEmbedderAccessible is sent when the new OuterDocAccessible is constructed, but that happens *before* we send the IPDL messages to destroy the old OuterDoc and add the new one.\nThis means that the old OuterDocAccessible is still the embedded document's parent when BrowserBridgeParent::RecvSetEmbedderAccessible executes.\nThus, we can't treat this as an error here.\nInstead, I've added a diagnostic assert to ensure that the embedded document doesn't have a parent when the new OuterDocAccessible is created, since by that time, the old OuterDocAccessible should have been removed.\nThis patch also fires a reorder event in AddChildDoc even for same-process documents.\nThis is necessary in order to write a reliable test, but it's probably better for clients too in case they happen to touch the re-created iframe in the short time before the embedded document is bound.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285198\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287276\n", "files": ["accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.cpp", "accessible/tests/browser/fission/browser.toml", "accessible/tests/browser/fission/browser_iframe_recreation.js", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": "f354ad0d84c9e21aede5ebbb303be076219f84e6", "git_parents": ["bf36ec337ff6fd84f86ad164f2ab44c972f01020"], "node": "6d6bfd17610d4174cdb1667b8c76be6299785694", "parents": ["f89353f2250a2bbef61321bcb7695dfdc67c8cc0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020094: Unify and correct the firing of reorder events for remote OuterDocAccessible.  a=pascalc\n\nPreviously, the content process fired reorder events for same-process embedded documents.\nHowever, this couldn't be done for out-of-process embedded documents because of the process boundary.\nThe content process also didn't fire a reorder event when the embedder was re-created.\nI attempted to solve this in bug 2019759 by having AddChildDoc fire a reorder event even for same-process embedded documents.\nUnfortunately, this resulted in the reorder event being fired before the embedded document's initial tree had been received in some cases.\nTo fix this:\n\n1. Don't fire reorder events on OuterDocAccessibles from the content process. Instead, let the parent process handle all reorder events for remote OuterDocAccessibles as described below, since it has a much clearer view of the various moving parts of the unified document tree.\n2. Set a flag when a remote document's initial tree has been received and attached in the parent process.\n3. Fire a single reorder event on the embedder when both the initial tree has been attached and the embedded document has been bound. These things can happen in either order, but both conditions must be met before the event is fired. This also includes firing a reorder event when the document is bound to a new embedder.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285378\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287277\n", "files": ["accessible/generic/DocAccessible.cpp", "accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.cpp", "accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.h"], "git_node": "d373b5611f76f542dd7bf989cc9d0dafb2bf14cf", "git_parents": ["f354ad0d84c9e21aede5ebbb303be076219f84e6"], "node": "93e0db439d14121f6d36cbe4d504d4b27b720d90", "parents": ["6d6bfd17610d4174cdb1667b8c76be6299785694"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2019763: When a new top level DocAccessibleParent is constructed for an OOP iframe, destroy the old top level DocAccessibleParent if there is one.  a=pascalc\n\nIn bug 1786496, we learned that during navigation, a new top level DocAccessibleParent can be constructed before the old one is destroyed.\nI don't know exactly how/why this happens, but it's not entirely unreasonable; destroying an old document should hardly take priority over loading the new one the user just requested.\nBug 1786496 fixed this for top level remote documents, but not for remote documents which are at the top level of their content process; i.e. OOP iframes.\nWhile speculative, it's reasonable to assume that this same issue might apply to OOP iframe documents.\nIf this does occur, when the BrowserBridgeParent version of AddChildDoc calls BrowserParent::GetTopLevelDocAccessibleParent to get the embedded document, it could end up with the old DocAccessibleParent (which might still be bound to its parent) instead of the new one.\nThis likely explains the \"Attempt to add child doc which already has a parent\" failure reported by AddChildDoc.\nAside from the content process crash, this would likely result in the OOP iframe being completely inaccessible in the parent process, since the new document would never be bound.\nTo fix this, apply the fix from bug 1786496 to all DocAccessibleParents at the top level of their content process, not just those at the very top of the remote tree.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285652\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287278\n", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp"], "git_node": "61366f2e92294d0f0fe3eea418af44495b67184f", "git_parents": ["d373b5611f76f542dd7bf989cc9d0dafb2bf14cf"], "node": "4b0454ecb33cf2983baea1fd8481c31d58c7cee2", "parents": ["93e0db439d14121f6d36cbe4d504d4b27b720d90"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773310061, "git_changesets": ["bf36ec337ff6fd84f86ad164f2ab44c972f01020", "f354ad0d84c9e21aede5ebbb303be076219f84e6", "d373b5611f76f542dd7bf989cc9d0dafb2bf14cf", "61366f2e92294d0f0fe3eea418af44495b67184f"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25038": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2018113.  a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287330\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/SourceSurfaceSharedData.cpp", "gfx/layers/SourceSurfaceSharedData.h"], "git_node": "d5cc24001280006363416f232762023955daa41d", "git_parents": ["61366f2e92294d0f0fe3eea418af44495b67184f"], "node": "78684c13145b983974b99286b8285cbba76a1c4c", "parents": ["4b0454ecb33cf2983baea1fd8481c31d58c7cee2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2018113.  a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287331\n", "files": ["dom/media/ipc/RemoteImageHolder.cpp", "gfx/layers/BufferTexture.cpp", "gfx/layers/ImageContainer.cpp", "gfx/layers/ImageDataSerializer.cpp", "gfx/layers/ImageDataSerializer.h", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/SharedPlanarYCbCrImage.cpp"], "git_node": "620730d8f2bff6333f4d60c8ac71dd96ae475d0d", "git_parents": ["d5cc24001280006363416f232762023955daa41d"], "node": "e98a2b00fc98ed5a89bd66329d37896c3c69e977", "parents": ["78684c13145b983974b99286b8285cbba76a1c4c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773323299, "git_changesets": ["d5cc24001280006363416f232762023955daa41d", "620730d8f2bff6333f4d60c8ac71dd96ae475d0d"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25039": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emma Zuehlcke \u003cemz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022221 - Do not reset allow list prefs when ETP strict feature list changes.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nWhen a Nimbus experiment modifies browser.contentblocking.features.strict\nor network.lna.etp.enabled after startup, the ContentBlockingPrefs\nobserver calls setPrefExpectationsAndUpdate() which resets all strict\ncategory prefs back to their defaults, including the user's allow list\nsettings.\n\nFix: change updateCBCategory and setPrefExpectationsAndUpdate to\npreserve allow list settings by default. Only the explicit user\ncategory-switch path (PREF_CB_CATEGORY observer) passes false to\nreset them, which is the intended behavior when a user actively\nchanges ETP categories.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287087\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287378\n", "files": ["browser/components/protections/ContentBlockingPrefs.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/antitracking/test/browser/browser_nimbus_etp_features.js"], "git_node": "f5711a289c07069ec7478a49f31b552e42c527c7", "git_parents": ["620730d8f2bff6333f4d60c8ac71dd96ae475d0d"], "node": "10e6a23f7c403812957ed60a31338905350e2092", "parents": ["e98a2b00fc98ed5a89bd66329d37896c3c69e977"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773327195, "git_changesets": ["f5711a289c07069ec7478a49f31b552e42c527c7"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25040": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2021592. Relax check for aCbCrSize to only what we need.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287332\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/ImageDataSerializer.cpp"], "git_node": "4eaceb0058f3a902371afc4bb89053212a4290b2", "git_parents": ["f5711a289c07069ec7478a49f31b552e42c527c7"], "node": "6c0920f31227e23d3a77ef0b06b9ec8b97403693", "parents": ["10e6a23f7c403812957ed60a31338905350e2092"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773327629, "git_changesets": ["4eaceb0058f3a902371afc4bb89053212a4290b2"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25041": {"changesets": [{"author":