3641567, "git_changesets": ["1143f7687ffa3c351e5ca3c8dc239fc6705e25af"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25081": {"changesets": [{"author": "mimi \u003cnsauermann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2014420 - Prevent focus restoration in Spotlight dialogs when tabbing to action buttons  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286712\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287616\n", "files": ["browser/components/aboutwelcome/content-src/components/ContentTiles.jsx", "browser/components/aboutwelcome/content/aboutwelcome.bundle.js", "browser/components/aboutwelcome/tests/unit/ContentTiles.test.jsx"], "git_node": "1e7919d0062b7da2c37402f6913c70e12f884c0d", "git_parents": ["1143f7687ffa3c351e5ca3c8dc239fc6705e25af"], "node": "e24e18844373bf471abb1f38f752fa90ef1251b1", "parents": ["d55a3054b5f846b5c435594f68d99db47ecaf7fd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641618, "git_changesets": ["1e7919d0062b7da2c37402f6913c70e12f884c0d"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25082": {"changesets": [{"author": "Roger Yang \u003croyang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023178 - Set report site issue feature for release to default true.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287581\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287614\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/nimbus.fml.yaml"], "git_node": "377e2faac7399b9e611f167800ea71ef418a289f", "git_parents": ["1e7919d0062b7da2c37402f6913c70e12f884c0d"], "node": "67f8d09a0401fd5c4752359de1f7bdacc460aa7d", "parents": ["e24e18844373bf471abb1f38f752fa90ef1251b1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641677, "git_changesets": ["377e2faac7399b9e611f167800ea71ef418a289f"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25083": {"changesets": [{"author": "Greg Stoll \u003cgreg@gregstoll.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022584 - avoid closing KsecDD for Trellix DLLs on ARM64  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nThe previous fix for this in bug 2008739 didn't have the right filenames\nfor ARM64.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287153\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287571\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/win/src/sandboxbroker/sandboxBroker.cpp"], "git_node": "2ec191decfdfbcb03eeda36e660ce6167a080d0d", "git_parents": ["377e2faac7399b9e611f167800ea71ef418a289f"], "node": "0f039419a457c5a09d846904e745df62c6d111b0", "parents": ["67f8d09a0401fd5c4752359de1f7bdacc460aa7d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641728, "git_changesets": ["2ec191decfdfbcb03eeda36e660ce6167a080d0d"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25084": {"changesets": [{"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020556 - Intermittent application crashed FinishReplacementChannelSetup  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nRedirectChannelRegistrar::GetOrCreate() can return null during shutdown.\nWe try to handle the null value gracefully and return NS_ERROR_ABORT\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286636\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287567\n", "files": ["netwerk/ipc/DocumentLoadListener.cpp", "netwerk/ipc/ParentChannelWrapper.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParent.cpp"], "git_node": "b429a5bb58f037a24a565f57fe758fc19ef317dd", "git_parents": ["2ec191decfdfbcb03eeda36e660ce6167a080d0d"], "node": "23ff1d8b639e26019adf067a967bed39fc1f516f", "parents": ["0f039419a457c5a09d846904e745df62c6d111b0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641771, "git_changesets": ["b429a5bb58f037a24a565f57fe758fc19ef317dd"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25085": {"changesets": [{"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020773 - Add structuredClone to the MV2 userScripts Sandbox wantGlobalProperties.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287444\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287564\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionContent.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "40dc21bb69e7e44b32a110458f1e257234803cd5", "git_parents": ["b429a5bb58f037a24a565f57fe758fc19ef317dd"], "node": "85b7085d4afb15202a641e141439c5af490c79e3", "parents": ["23ff1d8b639e26019adf067a967bed39fc1f516f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641819, "git_changesets": ["40dc21bb69e7e44b32a110458f1e257234803cd5"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25086": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022372 - Fix tabs.move when multiple tabs are moved  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nThis patch ensures that (if specified) `tabs.move()` returns both tabs\nof a split view, instead of just one (fix regression from bug 2017148).\n\nAs part of the fix, we ensure that the local `tabsToMove` array contains\nthe most relevant tabs even when a tab in that list is adopted. This\nfixes a long standing pre-existing issue, where calling `tabs.move()`\nwith the same tabId multiple times to a different window rejected with\nan unexpected error.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287049\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287560\n", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/parent/ext-tabs.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_tabs_move_window_multiple.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_tabs_splitViewId.js"], "git_node": "803e69c8de34d0e177966d2bcb1cb2e6f5a9ba6e", "git_parents": ["40dc21bb69e7e44b32a110458f1e257234803cd5"], "node": "040dd1c28ac1d926bd45ce0a7839e806cb50b094", "parents": ["85b7085d4afb15202a641e141439c5af490c79e3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641855, "git_changesets": ["803e69c8de34d0e177966d2bcb1cb2e6f5a9ba6e"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25087": {"changesets": [{"author": "Aaron Train \u003caaron.train@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022612 - Span API ends and trim devices in robo-arm config  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287221\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287379\n", "files": ["mobile/android/test_infra/flank-configs/fenix/arm-robo-test.yml"], "git_node": "64077985f6d32d6033811864b34daafd358af3c2", "git_parents": ["803e69c8de34d0e177966d2bcb1cb2e6f5a9ba6e"], "node": "5e092acc7cedee65a7c6c25794fafb3978781d81", "parents": ["040dd1c28ac1d926bd45ce0a7839e806cb50b094"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773641906, "git_changesets": ["64077985f6d32d6033811864b34daafd358af3c2"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25088": {"changesets": [{"author": "Vincent Hilla \u003cvhilla@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2021482 - Update nsCSPContext::mSelfURI later for initial about:blank.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286934\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287816\n", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "dom/security/test/csp/file_bug2021482_check.js", "dom/security/test/csp/file_bug2021482_sw.js", "dom/security/test/csp/mochitest.toml", "dom/security/test/csp/test_bug2021482.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/content-security-policy/inheritance/frame-src-javascript-url.html"], "git_node": "66168535f2300365434bd0d61b2e310384446a76", "git_parents": ["64077985f6d32d6033811864b34daafd358af3c2"], "node": "b28c37fce45a4b520d76b6ee89559dfed86047a7", "parents": ["5e092acc7cedee65a7c6c25794fafb3978781d81"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773642018, "git_changesets": ["66168535f2300365434bd0d61b2e310384446a76"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25089": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023383. Use image::SurfaceCache::IsLegalSize over gfx::Factory::AllowedSurfaceSize in SourceSurfaceSharedDataWrapper.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nSurfaceCache::IsLegalSize is what is used to determine if imgFrame's are valid, and that is what is on the content process side of this parent process code. So using the same function is what we want.\n\nPratically, on trunk SurfaceCache::IsLegalSize and Factory::AllowedSurfaceSize are basically identical (reject if one dimension is over 64k or total area can't fit in an int32_t), but that is only true after bug 1911583 which expanded that from 32k to 64k. But on esr140, that doesn't have bug 1911583, so these functions are different and we want to uplift the AllowedSurfaceSize check there.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287881\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/SourceSurfaceSharedData.cpp", "image/moz.build"], "git_node": "c127ad4a263bb5447a8802caf62bf013e6139f2d", "git_parents": ["66168535f2300365434bd0d61b2e310384446a76"], "node": "e04a62bfcbfabc8f31fa1bcbe80e7794f14451ca", "parents": ["b28c37fce45a4b520d76b6ee89559dfed86047a7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773642459, "git_changesets": ["c127ad4a263bb5447a8802caf62bf013e6139f2d"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25090": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022733 - WebTransportSessionProxy::mServerCertHashes cleanup,  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287298\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287915\n", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/webtransport/WebTransportSessionProxy.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/webtransport/WebTransportSessionProxy.h"], "git_node": "02da73ba5f7a8f8438624e0bb4657b0d9daf5f53", "git_parents": ["c127ad4a263bb5447a8802caf62bf013e6139f2d"], "node": "862d8bea8165d802f9e82904dd8f8c6076d8b800", "parents": ["e04a62bfcbfabc8f31fa1bcbe80e7794f14451ca"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773651409, "git_changesets": ["02da73ba5f7a8f8438624e0bb4657b0d9daf5f53"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25091": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2014304 - part2 : Fix P010/NV16 IOSurface readback for macOS tab thumbnail capture  a=pascalc\n\nCopyFromLockedMacIOSurface had no P010/NV16 handler, causing both formats to\nfall through to a raw BGRA memcpy and produce corrupted thumbnails.\n\nmacOS P010/NV16 IOSurfaces store 10-bit values in the high bits of each\nuint16_t (bits 15:6). We de-interleave the CbCr plane and use\nColorDepth::COLOR_16 (scale=256) so ConvertYCbCrToRGB maps them correctly\nto 8-bit output.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D284183\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285837\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/MacIOSurfaceHelpers.cpp"], "git_node": "300ea6471e0b86a514434ae2d83f6da22e338612", "git_parents": ["02da73ba5f7a8f8438624e0bb4657b0d9daf5f53"], "node": "060b97b1cfa9239e9a6fd9eacac621a39dbb02b3", "parents": ["862d8bea8165d802f9e82904dd8f8c6076d8b800"], "tags": []}], "date": 1773651571, "git_changesets": ["300ea6471e0b86a514434ae2d83f6da22e338612"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "25092": {"changesets": [{"author": "Release Engineering Landoscript \u003crelease+landoscript@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nach -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\naf -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nan -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nar -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nast -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\naz -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nbe -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nbg -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nbn -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nbr -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nbs -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nca -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\nca-valencia -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\ncak -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305e1959330f712ed7b240\ncs -\u003e 043d1e9ae91916d9a3305